    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - REMOVE -
        INPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="10">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303077">Figure 77</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303077" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1303077" filename="../figg13/G1303077.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 77. Input Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front bearing cover or upshift clutch brake plate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303078">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303078" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303078" filename="../figg13/G1303078.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Remove Front Bearing Cover or Upshift Clutch Brake Plate</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the drive gear and shaft as far forward as possible and remove the snap ring from the
                groove in the input shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303079">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303079" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303079" filename="../figg13/G1303079.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Move Drive Gear and Shaft as Far Forward as Possible</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a soft bar or rubber mallet, tap the input shaft through the bearing until it bottoms
                on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303080">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303080" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303080" filename="../figg13/G1303080.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Tap Input Shaft Through Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward while tapping the input shaft up and down with a rubber mallet
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303081">Figure 81</hotlnk>). Repeat steps 3 and 4 until the bearing is out of the
                bearing bore.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303081" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303081" filename="../figg13/G1303081.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Pull Input Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller or pry bars to remove the bearing from the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303082">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303082" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303082" filename="../figg13/G1303082.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Remove Bearing From Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer from the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303083">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303083" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303083" filename="../figg13/G1303083.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Remove Spacer From Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the inner diameter of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303084">Figure 84</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303084" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303084" filename="../figg13/G1303084.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 84. Remove Snap Ring From Inner Diameter of Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the shaft forward and from the splines of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303085">Figure 85</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303085" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303085" filename="../figg13/G1303085.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 85. Pull Shaft Forward and From Splines of Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the drive gear to the rear and against the 4th speed gear, engaging the splines of the
                sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303086">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303086" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1303086" filename="../figg13/G1303086.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 86. Move Drive Gear to Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
